{com}{sf}{ul off}{txt}
{com}. 
. * =====================================================================
. * LOAD DATA
. * =====================================================================
. 
. use tte/tte_example.dta, clear
{txt}
{com}. 
. * Package overview
. noisily tte, detail
{txt}
{hline 70}
{res}tte{txt} - Target Trial Emulation for Stata
Version 1.0.2
{hline 70}

{bf:Data Preparation}
  {hline 60}
{res}  tte_prepare{txt}   Map variable names, set estimand, validate
              data structure. Entry point for the pipeline.
              Stores metadata for downstream commands.

{res}  tte_validate{txt}  Comprehensive data quality checks: person-
              period format, gaps, treatment consistency,
              positivity, and missing data patterns.

{bf:Core Analysis}
  {hline 60}
{res}  tte_expand{txt}    Clone-censor-weight expansion into sequential
              emulated trials. Handles ITT, PP, and AT
              estimands with grace period support.

{res}  tte_weight{txt}    Stabilized inverse probability weights for
              treatment switching and informative censoring.
              Logistic models with truncation support.

{res}  tte_fit{txt}       Marginal structural model: pooled logistic
              regression or weighted Cox model. Flexible
              time specifications (linear/quadratic/ns).

{res}  tte_predict{txt}   Monte Carlo predictions from coefficient
              distribution. Cumulative incidence, survival,
              and risk differences with confidence intervals.

{bf:Diagnostics & Reporting}
  {hline 60}
{res}  tte_diagnose{txt}  Weight distribution, effective sample size,
              covariate balance (SMD), and positivity checks.

{res}  tte_plot{txt}      Visualization: KM curves, cumulative incidence,
              weight distributions, and Love plots.

{res}  tte_report{txt}    Publication-quality tables exportable to
              Excel or CSV format.

{res}  tte_protocol{txt}  Hernan 7-component protocol specification
              table for the methods section.

{hline 70}

{com}. 
. * =====================================================================
. * ANALYSIS 1: Intention-to-Treat (ITT)
. * =====================================================================
. * ITT ignores treatment switching — everyone analyzed as initially assigned.
. * No weights needed.
. 
. noisily display _newline
{res}

{txt}
{com}. noisily display as text "ITT ANALYSIS"
{res}{txt}ITT ANALYSIS

